ons of guest: neat appearance, making morn[ing] coffee (VN drinks 2 cups). Morning telephone calls to purveyors.*** Answering telephone. Example: "Here his secretary ("Elen Orska"). Vat? Gut.* Aisle usk." Knock on VN's door. Occasionally he answers the phone. At 9:00 PM three doors are locked: kitchen, "living," corner room. Kitchen key is taken by guest to her room in case of nighttime hunger (cf. Privileges) and is returned without fail early in the morning. * Washing cups (only), on Sunday mo